    Scope and Contents
Kastelic, daughter of Italian immigrants, discusses the circumstances of her first marriage in which she lived in extreme poverty and was severely abused. She also discusses the mining community near Kincaid, Illinois, mine wars, and the Progressive Miners of America Union. 1 tape, 35 mins., 20 pp. 
Interview by Sue Paso and Betty Bond, 1973 
